<subSubSection id="C3796513FFECFFF0FC8BFE03FBF6123E" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFECFFF0FC8BFE03FBF6123E" blockId="4.[869,1494,410,595]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFECFFF0FC8BFE03FC3011DE" bold="true" box="[869,994,410,435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Type data:</emphasis>
This variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFECFFF0FB7EFE03FAA511DE" authorityName="Moure et al." authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1168,1399,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFECFFF0FB7EFE03FAA511DE" box="[1168,1399,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Centris xanthocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a single male specimen collected in “Jundiahy” (= Jundiaí), southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFECFFF0FAEBFE43FA93119E" box="[1285,1345,474,499]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1DFFECFFF0FABEFE43FA18119E" box="[1360,1482,474,499]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1585,2076]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[94,1417,1585,2076]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Centrisxanthocnemis var.perflava Schrottky,1902 (holotype male).(A) Head,frontal view (scale bar:2 mm).(B) Habitus,dorsal view (scale bar:5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614966/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 3A, B</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFECFFF0FC7AFE63FC2B127E" box="[916,1017,506,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
is housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5DFFECFFF0FB64FE63FB18127E" box="[1162,1226,506,531]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
and it has the following data label: 97262 [printed]\ 1376 [handwritten]\ [red label without text].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796513FFECFFF0FC8BFDE3FAE3133E" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFECFFF0FC8BFDE3FAE3133E" blockId="4.[869,1494,634,851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFECFFF0FC8BFDE3FC3E12FE" bold="true" box="[869,1004,634,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Comments:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFECFFF0FBC9FDE3FB8B12FE" box="[1063,1113,634,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
specimen was caught by the insect collector Max Beron. It is a male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFECFFF0FACAFD03FA0412DE" authorityName="Moure et al." authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Perty" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1316,1494,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFECFFF0FACAFD03FA0412DE" box="[1316,1494,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. xanthocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with yellow pubescence on the mesosoma and hind legs instead of the blackish hairs found in most males. According to the accession book at MZSP the number 1,376 refers to the following data: “ 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFECFFF0FAE3FC83FA9F135E" box="[1293,1357,794,819]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFECFFF0FAB3FC83FA00135E" box="[1373,1490,794,819]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Jundiaí, M. Beron col” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFECFFF0FBB2FCA3FAF5133E" author="Ramos, K. S. &amp; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R." box="[1116,1319,826,851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="335 - 361" refId="ref4707" refString="Ramos, K. S.; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R. 2015. Type specimens of bees (Hymenoptera, Apidae) deposited in the Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 55 (24): 335 - 361. DOI" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ramos 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFECFFF0FB40FCA3FB35133E" box="[1198,1255,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.,</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
